hopobject.name: Page
hopobject.body: A financial advisor avalure cream review After a year of controversy at the BBC – Director-General George Entwistle resigning 54 days into the job, outrage about exorbitant pay-offs, anger over institutional bias – a satire that indulges in a spot of Beeb-bashing should be essential viewing. But while co-writers Robert Khan and Tom Salinsky – the pair behind last year’s so-so political hit Coalition – have their fingers on the topical pulse, Making News finds them struggling to tune into a theatrical wave-length that’s clear, dramatic and consistently funny.
